      "description": "The M\u00f6bius function is an important multiplicative function in number theory and combinatorics. The Riemann Hypothesis is equivalent to the statement that the sum of the M\u00f6bius function grows no faster than O(x^(1/2 + \u03b5)), representing massive cancellation.",
